         "1.0",
         "63.0",
         "CMS received a volumetric alert for thirty six IP addresses in address space 89.248.163.0/24. The space belongs to  RECYBER PROJECT NETBLOCK and resolves to domain of cyber[.]net located in Netherlands.\n\nCTI has determined that these IP addresses are known to perform scanning for various technologies including searching for Cisco ASAs, Open proxy, Socks5, conducting Nmap scans, attempting telnet logins and searching for various ways to create unauthenticated connections. CTI's research has not u",
         "False",
         "True",
         "False",
         null,
         null,
         "https://hvs.threatconnect.com/auth/indicators/details/address.xhtml?address=89.248.163.79&owner=HTOC+Org",
         "[{'id': 471298, 'name': 'DHA Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T13:42:01Z'}, {'id': 38933, 'name': 'Active Scanning: Scanning IP Blocks', 'description': 'Adversaries may scan victim IP blocks to gather information that can be used during targeting. Public IP addresses may be allocated to organizations by block, or a range of sequential addresses.\\n\\nAdversaries may scan IP blocks in order to [Gather Victim Network Information](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1590), such as which IP addresses are actively in use as well as more detailed information about hosts assigned these addresses. Scans may range from simple pings (ICMP requests and responses) to more nuanced scans that may reveal host software/versions via server banners or other network artifacts.(Citation: Botnet Scan) Information from these scans may reveal opportunities for other forms of reconnaissance (ex: [Search Open Websites/Domains](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1593) or [Search Open Technical Databases](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1596)), establishing operational resources (ex: [Develop Capabilities](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1587) or [Obtain Capabilities](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1588)), and/or initial access (ex: [External Remote Services](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1133)).', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-15T12:55:00Z', 'techniqueId': 'T1595.001', 'tactics': {'data': ['Reconnaissance'], 'count': 1}, 'platforms': {'data': ['PRE'], 'count': 1}}, {'id': 38932, 'name': 'Active Scanning', 'description': 'Adversaries may execute active reconnaissance scans to gather information that can be used during targeting. Active scans are those where the adversary probes victim infrastructure via network traffic, as opposed to other forms of reconnaissance that do not involve direct interaction.\\n\\nAdversaries may perform different forms of active scanning depending on what information they seek to gather. These scans can also be performed in various ways, including using native features of network protocols such as ICMP.(Citation: Botnet Scan)(Citation: OWASP Fingerprinting) Information from these scans may reveal opportunities for other forms of reconnaissance (ex: [Search Open Websites/Domains](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1593) or [Search Open Technical Databases](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1596)), establishing operational resources (ex: [Develop Capabilities](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1587) or [Obtain Capabilities](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1588)), and/or initial access (ex: [External Remote Services](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1133) or [Exploit Public-Facing Application](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1190)).', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-23T14:34:38Z', 'techniqueId': 'T1595', 'tactics': {'data': ['Reconnaissance'], 'count': 1}, 'platforms': {'data': ['PRE'], 'count': 1}}, {'id': 35760, 'name': 'OS Splunk API', 'description': 'Observations reported by the HHS Ofice of the Secretary (OS) Splunk Instance.', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T21:36:06Z'}, {'id': 35057, 'name': 'FDA Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-28T07:26:00Z'}, {'id': 30770, 'name': 'I&W', 'description': 'This tag is used specifically for HTOC I&W reports.', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-26T00:00:00Z'}, {'id': 30479, 'name': 'CMS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T03:22:32Z'}, {'id': 24004, 'name': 'vulnerability scanning', 'lastUsed': '2025-06-02T00:00:00Z'}, {'id': 23769, 'name': 'VA CSOC CTS Splunk', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T17:36:45Z'}, {'id': 23667, 'name': 'HRSA Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T05:05:42Z'}, {'id': 23630, 'name': 'NIH Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T15:38:09Z'}, {'id': 23586, 'name': 'IHS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T13:42:43Z'}, {'id': 23577, 'name': 'HHS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T06:30:44Z'}, {'id': 23576, 'name': 'Observed', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T00:00:00Z'}]",
