         "1.0",
         "50.0",
         "CMS received a Volumetrics alert regarding even IPs from the same IP block. These types of alerts generally indicate attacks where bad actors send enormous amounts of traffic to a targeted server, causing network congestion, packet loss and service disruptions--basically a DOS attack. \n\nCMS CTI investigated each IP but was unable to connect them to a particular threat actor or campaign. However, the historical nature of the indicators is known and documented and as such CMS blocked the indicator",
         "False",
         "True",
         "False",
